This paper involves the use of machine learning techniques to generate chord sequences from a symbolic melody. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of Sound (cs.SD) in the arXiv CS repository. Additionally, the paper involves the use of bidirectional long short-term memory (BLSTM) networks, which are a type of artificial neural network commonly used in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the use of feature extraction and normalization techniques, which are commonly used in the field of signal processing and machine learning (cs.SI). Furthermore, the paper involves the evaluation of the proposed method using quantitative and qualitative measures, which are commonly used in the field of machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves the use of user studies to evaluate the quality of the generated chord sequences, which is a common practice in the field of neural engineering (cs.NE).
